[Term]
id: SO:0002093
name: structural_interaction_variant
comment: Requested by Pablo Cingolani. The way I calculate this is simply by looking at the PDB entry of one protein and then marking those AA that are within 3 Angstrom of each other (and far away in the AA sequence, e.g. over 20 AA distance). The assumption is that, since they are very close in distance, they must be "interacting" and thus important for protein structure.
synonym: "structural interaction variant" EXACT []
is_a: SO:0001599 ! 3D_polypeptide_structure_variant
created_by: kareneilbeck
creation_date: 2016-03-07T11:43:55Z

